 A high court in Kaduna state has granted permission to Ibrahim El-Zakzaky, leader of the Islamic Movement in Nigeria (IMN), and his wife to travel to India for medical treatment. The IMN leader has been in detention since 2015 when he was arrested over the clash between his followers and some soldiers in Zaria, Kaduna state. The trial of El-Zakzaky and his wife is expected to resume as soon as they return from their medical treatment. They are facing an eight-count of culpable homicide, unlawful assembly, disturbance of public peace. The post Court grants Shiites leader, wife permission for medical trip to India appeared first on . Source: 36Ng